Summary of LDS Components and Modules
Category	Components/Modules
Wire Adapters	getRecord, getObjectInfo, getPicklistValues, getRecordUi
Functions	createRecord, updateRecord, deleteRecord, generateRecordInputForCreate/Update
Components	lightning-record-form, lightning-record-edit-form, lightning-record-view-form
Modules	lightning/uiRecordApi, lightning/uiObjectInfoApi, lightning/uiAppApi
Utilities	Field schema imports, error handling, Lightning Message Service


When to Use Each Component:
lightning-record-form:
Use when you need a single form that can switch between view and edit modes.
Example: A record detail page where users can view and edit records.

lightning-record-edit-form:
Use when you need a form specifically for creating or editing records.
Example: A form to create a new account or edit an existing account.

lightning-record-view-form:
Use when you need a read-only form to display record details.
Example: A summary page to display account information without editing capabilities.
